SIMPLE: individually
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Individually
<hw>In`di*vid"u*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an
individual manner or relation; as individuals; separately; each by
itself; <as>as, every person must apply <ex>individually</ex> for
admission</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Individually</xex> or
collectively.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How should that subsist solitarily by itself which hath no
substance, but <qex>individually</qex> the very same whereby others
subsist with it?</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In an inseparable manner; inseparably;
incommunicably; indivisibly; <as>as, <ex>individually</ex> the
same</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Omniscience], an attribute <qex>individually</qex> proper to the
Godhead.</q> <rj><qau>Hakewill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Individuate</ent>⟦br⟧
